## Problem

When a tool returns a non-JSON-serializable value (e.g. a `Buffer`, `undefined`, circular reference), the current error message is generic and doesn't indicate which tool failed or why.

## Expected behavior

Error should include: tool name, return type, and a hint about the valid return shape.

## Steps to reproduce

```ts
const agent = createAgent({
  tools: [{
    name: 'bad-tool',
    description: 'returns undefined',
    inputSchema: { type: 'object', properties: {} },
    execute: async () => undefined as any,
  }],
});
await agent.run('call bad-tool');
// Current: generic JS
